      <title>如何准备学术Presentation</title>
      <link href="/article/c3012411.html"/>
      <url>/article/c3012411.html</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>教学原地址：</p><p><a href="https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1WF411Y73C/?spm_id_from=333.788.recommend_more_video.-1&amp;vd_source=9b511b52d056fb21c406621247aed854">https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1WF411Y73C/?spm_id_from=333.788.recommend_more_video.-1&amp;vd_source=9b511b52d056fb21c406621247aed854</a></p><h1 id="PowerPoint-basics"><a href="#PowerPoint-basics" class="headerlink" title="PowerPoint basics"></a>PowerPoint basics</h1><ol><li><p>what font to use </p><ul><li><p>font <code>学术演讲应该用无衬线字体(san serif fonts)，而印刷书籍应该还用有衬线字体</code></p><ul><li><p>Arial</p></li><li><p>Comic sans</p></li><li><p>Trebuchet</p></li></ul></li><li><p>font size</p><ul><li><p>between 18 and 36</p></li><li><p>paper reference  → 14</p></li></ul></li><li><p>tips</p><ul><li>avoid capitalizing everything（不要把单词的每个字母都大写）</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>color</p><ul><li><p>it is better with a plain white background  and dark letters, either black or blue.</p></li><li><p>Streamline it down to as simple as possible and think about the contrast of letters.</p></li><li><p>a dark blue or black background works best for talks in a large room. </p></li><li><p>dark letters against a light background are best for smaller rooms or teaching</p></li></ul></li><li><p>layout</p><ul><li><p>Every slide should have a heading. The best heading is a simple senetence.</p></li><li><p>Limit text blocks to no more than two lines each.( 引用经典语句除外 )</p></li><li><p>Lists should be short, try to limit your lists to just three items. Avoid like mad long lists</p></li><li><p>Unveil your list one at a time. Use animation to unveil your list one by one.</p></li><li><p>Be very generous in a slide with empty space.</p></li><li><p>Try your best to include a simple image on every slide.</p></li><li><p>Limit the number of items on each slide. Each slide should make just on or two points. </p></li><li><p>Simple rule: If you’re not going to take the time to explain it ,get rid of it.</p></li><li><p>Avoid fancy transitions between slides unless you have a good reason.</p></li><li><p>Don’t drown the audience with data. Less is more. Just the data that you need to convince the audience of the credibility of your science.</p></li></ul></li></ol><h1 id="How-to-structure-a-good-talk"><a href="#How-to-structure-a-good-talk" class="headerlink" title="How to structure a good talk"></a>How to structure a good talk</h1><ol><li><p>The structure of a good talk: start broad, get specific, end broad.</p></li><li><p>Use a “home slide” at each major trasition in your talk.</p></li></ol><h1 id="Example"><a href="#Example" class="headerlink" title="Example"></a>Example</h1><p><a href="https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV12Y4y1k75i/?spm_id_from=333.337.search-card.all.click&amp;vd_source=9b511b52d056fb21c406621247aed854">https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV12Y4y1k75i/?spm_id_from=333.337.search-card.all.click&amp;vd_source=9b511b52d056fb21c406621247aed854</a></p>]]></content>
      
      
